 </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Young Ones Gathering</span><hr size=1> Indeed it was both chilling and thrilling to encounter an invader so close to our mainland.  The cowardly Elf waited till our warriors were engaged in melee combat and used that opportunity to backstab our healer (Traxd) and runemaster (Abbatoir), and then run away.  Nor and I gave chase as soon as the rest of our group was secure from the creature we were fighting, but the Elf was far ahead of us by then.  If I had had me wits about me to sing my song of speed without delay, we might have caught him. As it happens we did get a few hits in on him before he &quot;vanished into the shadows&quot;. We returned to our group and began a search for a healer, but the invader struck a second time and finished the rest of us off.  One hit to me was with a dagger for 450 points of damage in a single blow!<br>
<br>
The enemy did employ good sniper tactics, and I give that credit to him. There were several lessons learned that night, which have prompted me to start a new thread called &quot;Baisc Strategy for RvR&quot; which I think might benefit the whole guild.<br>
<br>
Death to Invaders!!<br>
